WEBVTT

00:04.338 --> 00:06.107
Okay, Dave, as a doctor,

00:06.174 --> 00:08.209
I've got
an unfair advantage
in this game

00:08.276 --> 00:09.610
because
I'm a master of medical...

00:09.677 --> 00:11.279
(BUZZES)
Dang it!

00:11.812 --> 00:13.047
(SIGHS)

00:13.114 --> 00:15.916
It's okay, Dad.
I like playing
Operation with you.

00:15.983 --> 00:18.452
I finally get to know
what victory tastes like.

00:21.622 --> 00:23.091
(SIGHS)

00:23.157 --> 00:26.060
Here we go.
Funny bone.
Gets me every time.

00:26.127 --> 00:27.728
Maybe 'cause
you don't have one.

00:27.795 --> 00:31.031
Everyone has
a funny bone, Dave.
Except Scandinavians.

00:31.099 --> 00:32.700
(BOTH LAUGHING)

00:34.168 --> 00:35.936
You're hilarious, Dad.

00:36.003 --> 00:37.805
I know. (CHUCKLES)

00:39.140 --> 00:40.608
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

00:40.674 --> 00:42.576
Dad, is sex
just for making a baby?

00:42.643 --> 00:44.145
(BUZZING)

00:46.380 --> 00:48.549
Oh, sorry, buddy.
I couldn't hear you.

00:48.616 --> 00:50.184
You know,
I'm focused on the game.

00:50.251 --> 00:51.685
Is sex...
(BUZZING)

00:51.752 --> 00:54.322
(LOUDLY) Is sex
just for making a baby?

00:57.091 --> 00:59.260
Well, son,
the thing about that is,

00:59.327 --> 01:01.329
there's birds, bees...

01:01.395 --> 01:02.796
(IMITATING SNORING)

01:08.802 --> 01:10.571
(SNORING CONTINUES)

01:14.041 --> 01:15.443
Man,
if I hadn't whipped out

01:15.509 --> 01:17.178
the old
"pretend to be asleep"
trick,

01:17.245 --> 01:19.880
there's no telling
where that conversation
would've gone. (CHUCKLES)

01:19.947 --> 01:22.683
It might've gone to you
having the sex talk
with your son.

01:22.750 --> 01:24.051
Why didn't you do it?

01:24.118 --> 01:26.554
(IMITATING SNORING)

01:26.620 --> 01:29.723
It didn't work
during couple's therapy,
and it's not working now.

01:31.259 --> 01:33.227
I just don't think Dave's
ready for that stuff.

01:33.294 --> 01:34.895
If he's old enough
to ask the questions,

01:34.962 --> 01:36.364
he's old enough
to hear the answers.

01:36.430 --> 01:37.831
Plus,
you promised you'd do it.

01:37.898 --> 01:40.234
You know I need
to work up to things!

01:40.301 --> 01:41.635
Yeah, I know.

01:41.702 --> 01:43.204
You still haven't taken down
the Christmas lights,

01:43.271 --> 01:45.206
and it's almost April.

01:45.273 --> 01:48.476
I don't let a calendar
rule my life, Allison.
I'm not a Mayan.

01:50.077 --> 01:52.680
Besides, I'm not
the only one that's shirking.

01:52.746 --> 01:54.782
You are supposed
to give Molly the sex talk.

01:54.848 --> 01:56.750
And I did.
Six years ago.

01:56.817 --> 01:58.352
Really? How'd it go?

01:58.419 --> 02:00.087
Awkward but informative.

02:00.154 --> 02:01.822
Do you want me
to give Dave the talk?

02:02.656 --> 02:03.924
Yes.
No.

02:05.259 --> 02:06.460
Fine.

02:06.527 --> 02:09.029
I'll teach the boy
about the horizontal arts.

02:09.096 --> 02:10.931
Puke.

02:10.998 --> 02:13.301
And, in the spirit of things
you said you'd do,

02:13.367 --> 02:14.968
maybe take down
the Christmas lights.

02:15.035 --> 02:17.338
Oh, and what about getting
the brakes replaced
in my car?

02:17.405 --> 02:18.872
When'd you ask me
to do that?

02:18.939 --> 02:21.242
Like, a year ago.

02:21.309 --> 02:24.545
The warning light's
been on so long,
the bulb blew out.

02:24.612 --> 02:26.180
Or did the brakes
fix themselves,

02:26.247 --> 02:28.081
like I said
might happen?

02:28.148 --> 02:29.317
(CELLPHONE DINGS)

02:31.051 --> 02:32.220
Oh, snap!

02:32.286 --> 02:33.721
The Rutledges
can't use their tickets

02:33.787 --> 02:35.923
to the Doobie Brothers
concert tonight!

02:35.989 --> 02:37.558
(GASPS)
What do you say?

02:37.625 --> 02:38.959
You up for takin' it
to the streets?

02:39.026 --> 02:41.229
(LAUGHS)
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

02:41.295 --> 02:42.930
Let's Listen
to the music!
(GRUNTS)

02:42.996 --> 02:44.765
Okay, I don't know
what's happening,

02:44.832 --> 02:48.168
but I know it's dorky
and forced.

02:48.236 --> 02:50.771
Besides, Taylor's mom
is taking us
to SAT prep tonight,

02:50.838 --> 02:52.740
so FYI,
I can't watch Dave.

02:52.806 --> 02:54.775
Hmm. Think you can find
a sitter?

02:54.842 --> 02:56.109
Or you could.

02:56.176 --> 02:58.679
Fine. I'll get
a babysitter...
Mmm.

02:58.746 --> 03:00.548
...and tell Dave about sex

03:00.614 --> 03:03.217
and get your
warning light fixed.

03:03.284 --> 03:05.986
It's not the
brake warning light
that's the issue.

03:06.053 --> 03:08.456
Yeah, it'll fix itself,
like the brakes did.

03:08.522 --> 03:10.724
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

03:10.791 --> 03:13.427
New sweater?
Yeah.
What do you think?

03:13.494 --> 03:15.028
(INHALES DEEPLY)

03:15.095 --> 03:16.364
Have a good day, Mom.

03:19.132 --> 03:21.502
Wait.
What's wrong
with my sweater?

03:21.569 --> 03:23.471
(SIGHS)
Here's the thing.

03:23.537 --> 03:26.039
You've really been
dressing like
a mom lately,

03:26.106 --> 03:27.508
and I mean like
a mom-mom,

03:27.575 --> 03:29.243
not like
a Jessica Alba mom.

03:30.511 --> 03:31.912
What are you
talking about?

03:31.979 --> 03:33.781
It seems like
some moms hit a point

03:33.847 --> 03:36.484
where they start
prioritizing comfort
over style.

03:36.550 --> 03:40.921
Symptoms include
boxy sweaters,
drawstring pants, clogs...

03:42.523 --> 03:44.258
And so, so much linen.

03:46.159 --> 03:47.695
Come on, Mom,
I'll take you shopping.

03:47.761 --> 03:49.663
This is a cry for help.

03:49.730 --> 03:50.898
But I heard it.

03:52.733 --> 03:54.668
Hey, I like my look.

03:54.735 --> 03:56.970
I saw this scarf
in a magazine,
thank you very much.

03:57.037 --> 03:58.038
Which magazine?

03:58.672 --> 04:00.007
Giving Up.

04:00.073 --> 04:01.309
(SCOFFS)

04:01.375 --> 04:03.243
It's a yoga magazine

04:03.311 --> 04:05.479
about giving yourself up
to the practice!

04:05.546 --> 04:06.914
Don't take it
out of con...

04:13.887 --> 04:17.358
No, Mrs. Pancake.
I just wanted to see
if you could babysit.

04:17.425 --> 04:20.628
No, please don't give me
your social security number.
(STUTTERS)

04:20.694 --> 04:22.162
Okay, hanging up now.

04:23.464 --> 04:24.698
What's going on?

04:24.765 --> 04:26.099
Well, good news,

04:26.166 --> 04:29.136
I think I just sold
my elderly neighbor
a reverse mortgage.

04:31.305 --> 04:33.206
Bad news,
she was my last hope

04:33.273 --> 04:34.608
at getting a sitter
for tonight.

04:34.675 --> 04:37.411
Oh, I could watch Dave.
I love kids.

04:37.478 --> 04:38.679
You don't have plans?

04:38.746 --> 04:40.013
No.

04:40.080 --> 04:42.383
But thanks for pretending
like you thought I might.

04:43.551 --> 04:44.785
You're welcome.
(CHUCKLES)

04:48.188 --> 04:51.859
At lunch, do you guys
think you could help me
with my online dating profile?

04:51.925 --> 04:54.127
I am attracting
the wrong matches.

04:54.194 --> 04:55.863
What does your profile
say now?

04:55.929 --> 04:58.165
(READING)
"Smart, fun gal...
Mmm-hmm.

04:58.231 --> 05:00.934
"...seeks rock-hard guy
who can stay up
all night.

05:02.102 --> 05:03.904
"Must not mind
sharing a bed

05:03.971 --> 05:06.239
"with my two best friends,
Marissa and Karen."

05:08.542 --> 05:11.078
What?
I want a solid,
stable guy

05:11.144 --> 05:15.115
who likes to
stay up late talking
and playing with my cats.

05:15.182 --> 05:17.618
Yeah,
that's not coming across.

05:17.685 --> 05:20.153
Ooh, maybe I should
come up with
a different word for "cats."

05:20.220 --> 05:21.422
BOTH: No!

05:23.957 --> 05:25.626
Listen, girl,
I would love
to stay and help,

05:25.693 --> 05:28.095
but I'm having lunch
with my dreamboat B.F.
JULIE: Oh.

05:28.161 --> 05:29.697
Story checks out.
(GASPS)

05:29.763 --> 05:31.098
Ah.

05:33.401 --> 05:34.968
You guys are too cute.

05:35.035 --> 05:36.570
I mean that literally.
Dial it down.

05:37.838 --> 05:39.440
This is a place
of business,

05:39.507 --> 05:41.942
and, yeah,
I know Damona and I
boned a bunch of times,

05:42.009 --> 05:43.310
but that was different.

05:43.377 --> 05:45.413
I'm the boss.

05:45.479 --> 05:46.914
So, where are you two
going for lunch?

05:46.980 --> 05:48.449
(SIGHS)
Mmm, I don't know.
What do you feel like, hon?

05:48.516 --> 05:50.117
Oh, I don't care.
You pick something.

05:50.183 --> 05:51.419
Well, I want
whatever you want,
so we're back to you.

05:51.485 --> 05:52.920
Well, you pick.
You. No, you pick.

05:52.986 --> 05:54.455
No, I can't pick.
You do it.
You do it.

05:54.522 --> 05:55.756
Oh, oh, all right.

05:55.823 --> 05:57.257
Tie.
No tie here.

05:57.324 --> 05:58.759
You win! (CHUCKLES)
Let's go.

05:58.826 --> 06:00.594
All right, bye, guys.
Nice to see you.

06:00.661 --> 06:03.030
Yeah, and listen,
I'm sorry you guys
had to witness our fight.

06:08.736 --> 06:10.237
(DOORBELL RINGS)

06:12.840 --> 06:14.675
Oh, hey!
You must be
Taylor's mom.

06:14.742 --> 06:16.610
Come on in.
I'm Allison.

06:16.677 --> 06:18.912
I'm Grace.
Nice to meet you.

06:18.979 --> 06:20.347
Molly will be down
in a second.

06:20.414 --> 06:21.949
Thanks for taking
the girls to class.

06:22.015 --> 06:24.017
Please, don't thank me.

06:24.084 --> 06:26.386
With the other five
at home, any excuse
to get out of the house.

06:27.821 --> 06:30.323
I'm sorry.
I'm a bit of a mess today.

06:30.390 --> 06:32.526
I haven't had a shower
since the weekend.

06:34.161 --> 06:35.195
Got any wine?

06:36.029 --> 06:37.297
Oh, I...

06:37.364 --> 06:40.200
Oh, look!
We're sweater twins!

06:41.802 --> 06:43.771
Hey, how about that?

06:43.837 --> 06:45.105
Sweater twins!

06:48.008 --> 06:49.743
Oh, and great clogs.

06:49.810 --> 06:51.111
I live in clogs.

06:51.178 --> 06:53.380
I love not having laces
to deal with.

06:54.314 --> 06:57.217
Bending over's the worst!

06:57.284 --> 06:59.286
Yeah, bending over
is pretty terrible.

06:59.352 --> 07:00.721
All right, you guys,
have fun.

07:02.456 --> 07:03.624
Okay!

07:03.691 --> 07:05.659
See you later, Mom.

07:10.197 --> 07:12.399
And make sure
he's in bed by 10:00.

07:12.466 --> 07:14.502
Do I have to go
to bed by 10:00?

07:14.568 --> 07:17.270
It might be tough
to squeeze in
all our activities.

07:17.337 --> 07:21.875
I brought
math flashcards and
a terrarium-making kit.

07:21.942 --> 07:24.177
Do I have to stay up
till 10:00?

07:25.012 --> 07:26.514
Aww, you!

07:26.580 --> 07:28.148
We're gonna have
a ball!

07:28.215 --> 07:29.282
I'm so sorry.

07:29.349 --> 07:31.151
Okay!
We should head out.

07:31.218 --> 07:32.553
Have fun, you two.

07:32.620 --> 07:35.856
(LAUGHS)
Oh, my God, hilarious!

07:35.923 --> 07:38.526
You almost wore
that old throw blanket
out of the house!

07:38.592 --> 07:40.694
(LAUGHS)
It's a shawl-sweater.

07:40.761 --> 07:42.262
Ooh, it's stunning!

07:45.699 --> 07:47.334
(DOOR CLOSES)
Okay.

07:47.400 --> 07:49.436
What should
we do first?

07:49.503 --> 07:50.938
Is sex
just for making a baby?

08:01.014 --> 08:02.783
Hey, what's wrong
with you?

08:02.850 --> 08:05.653
Oh, hi. (STUTTERS)
I just got this text
from Connor,

08:05.719 --> 08:08.522
saying that he's coming by
because "we need to talk."

08:08.589 --> 08:11.625
So?
So, obviously,
he's breaking up with me!

08:11.692 --> 08:13.594
Or maybe he misses
your beautiful face.

08:13.661 --> 08:15.228
No, I don't think
that's it because
I texted him,

08:15.295 --> 08:16.797
"Is it because
you miss
my beautiful face?"

08:16.864 --> 08:18.799
And then he texted
me back, "No!"

08:20.367 --> 08:22.670
Well, either way,
I'm sure it's nothing, Clark.

08:22.736 --> 08:24.071
Yeah, listen to Damona.

08:24.137 --> 08:26.339
She's a very wise woman,
and she's never wrong.

08:26.406 --> 08:28.375
Thank you, Pat.
(CHUCKLES)

08:28.441 --> 08:29.810
You're doomed.

08:32.546 --> 08:34.314
Whoa,
what's wrong
with you?

08:34.381 --> 08:38.085
I was babysitting
for Dr. Ken,
and I really screwed up.

08:38.151 --> 08:40.220
Let me guess.
There was
an unmarked pill bottle,

08:40.287 --> 08:42.723
and you accidentally took
a bunch of Dr. Ken's
growth hormones?

08:43.957 --> 08:45.859
Well,
don't worry about it.

08:45.926 --> 08:47.728
They're obviously
ineffective.

08:49.162 --> 08:52.165
No, I gave Dave
the sex talk.

08:52.232 --> 08:53.767
What? Why?

08:53.834 --> 08:55.736
(SIGHS)
He started asking me
all these questions,

08:55.803 --> 08:57.370
one after another.

08:57.437 --> 08:59.139
I thought it was only
a few minutes,

08:59.206 --> 09:01.742
but then I looked
at my phone, and it had
been two hours.

09:02.275 --> 09:04.077
Two hours?

09:04.144 --> 09:07.748
The sex talk
my dad gave me
lasted 25 cents.

09:07.815 --> 09:08.916
As soon as that
was used up,

09:08.982 --> 09:10.751
the curtain came down,
and that was that.

09:11.919 --> 09:13.220
Girl,
what were you thinking?

09:13.286 --> 09:14.988
Ugh, I don't know!

09:15.055 --> 09:18.558
Once I start talking,
I mean, I'm just
a very oral person.

09:20.260 --> 09:22.663
That is not a bad thing.

09:22.730 --> 09:24.497
You wouldn't believe
how many people

09:24.564 --> 09:26.333
responded to that
on my dating profile.

09:30.337 --> 09:31.571
(SIGHS)

09:31.639 --> 09:32.940
Take me shopping.

09:33.741 --> 09:35.408
Oh, I would, Mom,

09:35.475 --> 09:38.345
but Linen On The Edge
went out of business
six years ago.

09:39.412 --> 09:40.881
I'm serious.

09:40.948 --> 09:43.250
Taylor's mom was
a real wake-up call.

09:43.316 --> 09:46.954
Not to mention the 300
other moms I saw
at the Doobie Brothers show.

09:47.020 --> 09:48.221
Also...

09:48.288 --> 09:51.692
One of the Doobie Brothers
was wearing my scarf.

09:51.759 --> 09:54.261
Are you ready for people
to be able to tell
what gender you are

09:54.327 --> 09:55.729
from more than
20 feet away?

09:56.864 --> 09:58.365
I am.

09:58.431 --> 10:00.600
Congratulations.
The hardest part is over.

10:00.668 --> 10:03.737
Just be warned, whatever
you wear to the store
ain't coming home,

10:03.804 --> 10:06.740
so you can kiss
that sexy little burnt
pumpkin number goodbye.

10:10.310 --> 10:11.712
Hey, Mom,
just wanted you to know,

10:11.779 --> 10:13.747
I'm all up to speed
on sex stuff now.

10:13.814 --> 10:15.448
Way to not be weird
about it.

10:18.385 --> 10:20.020
Hey!
You finally did it!

10:20.087 --> 10:22.389
Yep.
What'd I do?

10:22.455 --> 10:24.024
Dave said he knows
all about sex.

10:25.125 --> 10:26.694
Oh. Right.

10:26.760 --> 10:28.128
Yep. I did it.

10:28.195 --> 10:29.763
At first...

10:29.830 --> 10:31.932
(IMITATING GEORGE BUSH)
Not gonna do it,
but I did.

10:31.999 --> 10:34.067
(CHUCKLES)
Wow. I'm so proud.

10:35.135 --> 10:36.303
Way to dad up!

10:36.369 --> 10:37.570
(CHUCKLES)

10:37.637 --> 10:38.806
(DOOR CLOSES)

10:43.276 --> 10:45.112
Dave, how did you
learn about sex?

10:45.178 --> 10:47.647
From Julie.
She lectured me
for about an hour,

10:47.715 --> 10:49.316
followed by
a spirited Q&A.

10:55.055 --> 10:57.090
I mean, why does he want
to break up with me?

10:57.157 --> 10:59.626
Look, you've only got
one option here...
(SIGHS)

10:59.693 --> 11:00.894
...a PEB.

11:00.961 --> 11:03.563
A what?
A preemptive breakup.

11:03.630 --> 11:04.832
Yeah.

11:04.898 --> 11:06.233
When you think
someone's gonna
dump you,

11:06.299 --> 11:07.634
you beat them
to the punch.
Hmm.

11:07.701 --> 11:09.436
Take control
of the narrative,
as in,

11:09.502 --> 11:11.604
"Hey, did you hear Clark
dumped that fella?

11:11.671 --> 11:13.874
"He is not
to be trifled with."

11:13.941 --> 11:18.278
That is the dumbest thing
I have ever heard!

11:18.345 --> 11:19.980
"Preemptive breakup?"

11:20.047 --> 11:21.448
What if Connor
doesn't want
to break up with you?

11:21.514 --> 11:24.351
No. He does.
I know it.

11:24.417 --> 11:26.086
I've been on
the business end
of too many

11:26.153 --> 11:27.587
"we need to talk" talks.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.691
The PEB is the way to go.

11:31.759 --> 11:33.126
Thank you, Pat.

11:34.627 --> 11:36.329
You're welcome.

11:36.396 --> 11:40.000
So, this is what
it feels like
to help people.

11:40.067 --> 11:41.268
I don't care for it.

11:45.338 --> 11:46.940
Julie, we need to talk.

11:47.007 --> 11:49.342
Will everyone
please stop
saying that?

11:53.613 --> 11:56.049
Dr. Ken, I am so sorry.

11:56.116 --> 11:58.185
I've already
packed my things.

11:58.251 --> 11:59.686
Somebody...

11:59.753 --> 12:01.421
Take good care
of Plant!

12:02.923 --> 12:04.491
Oh, no, I'm not mad.

12:04.557 --> 12:06.359
You did me a solid.

12:06.426 --> 12:07.961
I've been dreading
having that conversation
with Dave.

12:08.028 --> 12:09.296
Really?

12:09.362 --> 12:10.964
Oh, but what
about Allison?
Is she mad at me?

12:11.031 --> 12:12.199
Oh, she doesn't know.

12:12.265 --> 12:14.067
She assumed I gave Dave
the sex talk,

12:14.134 --> 12:15.668
and I did not
correct her.

12:15.735 --> 12:18.538
She hates being corrected,
and I hate being caught.
(CHUCKLES)

12:19.272 --> 12:21.108
Oh, God,
I'm so relieved!

12:21.174 --> 12:24.144
I mean, she would've
been hella pissed,
but don't worry.

12:24.211 --> 12:26.780
I would never put you
in the path
of that Mama Bear.

12:28.115 --> 12:29.549
(CELLPHONE BUZZING)
Oh.

12:29.616 --> 12:31.384
Oh. Hey, Allison.

12:31.451 --> 12:33.686
I just got a call
from Principal Michaels.

12:33.753 --> 12:35.155
Apparently,
there's an issue
with Dave

12:35.222 --> 12:37.157
talking to his
classmates about sex.

12:37.224 --> 12:39.626
Well, that was
bound to happen.
I was the same way.

12:39.692 --> 12:42.562
When I learned about sex,
I wouldn't shut up about it.
(CHUCKLES)

12:42.629 --> 12:44.297
Ask any of my
med-school friends.

12:46.867 --> 12:49.669
Okay, that's sad,
but it's not the issue.

12:49.736 --> 12:53.140
The problem is, apparently,
he's wrong about things.

12:53.206 --> 12:54.942
Like, really wrong.

12:55.008 --> 12:57.044
What did you tell him?

12:57.110 --> 12:58.778
I didn't tell Dave anything!
It was Julie!

12:58.846 --> 13:00.147
(STUTTERS)

13:09.957 --> 13:11.524
You didn't have to come
all the way here.

13:11.591 --> 13:13.260
Oh, no, I wanted to.

13:13.326 --> 13:15.328
I'm just so sorry.

13:15.395 --> 13:18.065
I, I didn't plan to talk
to Dave about sex.

13:18.131 --> 13:21.468
I even tried to distract him
with a baking soda volcano,

13:21.534 --> 13:24.337
but the eruption
led to more questions.

13:26.339 --> 13:29.442
I know how persistent
Dave can be
when he's curious.

13:29.509 --> 13:33.413
We once drove 200 miles
to the Museum of Scones.
Yeah.

13:33.480 --> 13:36.016
It's a huge racket.
They don't sell jam.

13:36.083 --> 13:38.418
You can't bring
your own.

13:38.485 --> 13:40.020
What I don't
understand is

13:40.087 --> 13:42.655
